We hadn&#39;t considered this need to crawl domains only resolvable by the  
proxy before. So, it would take some trickery (supply fake DNS to the  
crawler) or new code to enable this.

Perhaps the code could be as little as a beanshell script processor  
inserted instead of (or before or after) FetchDNS. Alternatively,  
perhaps changes to PreconditionEnforcer or FetchDNS would do the  
trick, if you&#39;re comfortable tweaking the Java code.

- Gordon


